  # Missing mail form


  The page offers an online editor for a lost-package form. Users can open the form,
  type into fields, add images or comments, sign it electronically, and then export
  or share the completed document.


  ## Form Identity and Delivery Mechanism


  - form reference: `113997-lost-package-form`;

  - submission channel: `editor_export_or_share`.


  These values identify the particular form instance and the mechanism through which
  a completed document leaves the editor. They do not, by themselves, establish whether
  USPS operates or authorizes that channel.


  ## Lost Package Form


  The form is described as a lost or damaged package claim form. It asks for information
  such as:


  - order number;

  - name;

  - email address;

  - telephone number;

  - shipping carrier;

  - whether the issue is a stolen, lost, or damaged item;

  - description of the claim;

  - amount of the claim;

  - preferred reimbursement method;

  - signature and date.


  The shipping-carrier choices include UPS and USPS, so the form appears operationally
  capable of collecting the type of information used in a parcel-recovery request.


  ## How the Online Editor Works


  The page instructs users to select **Get Form**, complete the document, sign it,
  and then use the editor''s export or sharing controls. Available sharing methods
  include email, link, fax, download, and print.


  The page includes search-related wording such as:


  - lost package form USPS;

  - missing mail search request;

  - USPS missing mail;

  - USPS online help request form;

  - report missing package USPS;

  - USPS Missing Mail form online.


  The page describes the form and its delivery mechanism, but a separate authority
  check is needed to determine who operates this specific channel and whether USPS
  has delegated shipment-recovery submissions to it.

